My meme

# static meme

# frame 1 

# top and bottom row image frame
drake_top <- image_read("https://i.imgflip.com/t7px7.jpg?a474240") %>%
  image_scale(500)

drake_bottom <- image_read("https://i.cbc.ca/1.3279853.1532811524!/fileImage/httpImage/drake.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(500)

# top and bottom text frames including text
top_text <- image_blank(width = 500, height = 347, color = "#ead61c") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Starting\nproject a week\n early", color = "#000000", size = 60, font = "Arial", gravity = "center")

bot_text <- image_blank(width = 500, height = 350, color = "#ead61c") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Starting\nproject 3\ndays before\ndeadline", color = "#000000", size = 60, font = "Arial", gravity = "center")

# combining top and bottom image frames
first_column <- c(drake_top, drake_bottom) %>%
  image_append(stack = TRUE)

# combining top and bottom text frames
second_column <- c(top_text, bot_text) %>%
  image_append(stack = TRUE)

# combining both columns into a single frame
frame1 <- c(first_column, second_column) %>%
  image_append()

image_write(frame1, "my_meme.png")

frame1

# animated meme

# frame 2

# new top and bottom text frames
top_text2 <- image_blank(width = 500, height = 347, color = "#ead61c") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "2 days\n till deadline", color = "#000000", size = 60, font = "Arial", gravity = "center")

bot_text2 <- image_blank(width = 500, height = 350, color = "#ead61c") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "4 hours\n till deadline", color = "#000000", size = 60, font = "Arial", gravity = "center")

# combining new top and bottom text frames into a column
second_column2 <- c(top_text2, bot_text2) %>%
  image_append(stack = TRUE)

# combining image column with new text column
frame2 <- c(first_column, second_column2) %>%
  image_append()



# frame 3

# new image frame for frame 3
glasses <- image_read("https://i.kym-cdn.com/photos/images/newsfeed/001/553/696/a42.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(350)

# new top and bottom text frames
top_text3 <- image_blank(width = 500, height = 347, color = "#ead61c") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "3 hours\n till deadline", color = "#000000", size = 60, font = "Arial", gravity = "center")

bot_text3 <- image_blank(width = 500, height = 350, color = "#ead61c") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Actually starting\n the project", color = "#000000", size = 60, font = "Arial", gravity = "center")

# combining left and right columns
first_column3 <- c(drake_top, glasses) %>%
  image_append(stack = TRUE)

second_column3 <- c(top_text3, bot_text3) %>%
  image_append(stack = TRUE)

# combining left and right columns for frame 3
frame3 <- c(first_column3, second_column3) %>%
  image_append()


# frame 4

# setting 2 new images for the frame
studying <- image_read("https://i.imgflip.com/5c2brr.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(500)

sweat <- image_read("https://pbs.twimg.com/media/F0Y4WciaMAYpWqS.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(500)

# generate 2 columns, left and right for combining
left <- c(studying, sweat) %>%
  image_append(stack = TRUE)

right <- c(sweat, studying) %>%
  image_append(stack = TRUE)

# combining left and right columns
frame4 <- c(left, right) %>%
  image_append()


# frame 5

# new image frame for frame 5
cry <- image_read("https://i.ytimg.com/vi/xPM85MCgqXo/hqdefault.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(500)

# dividing the text between text1 and text2 so the text is spread evenly
text1 <- image_blank(width = 500, height = 150, color = "#ead61c") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Not submitting", color = "#000000", size = 60, font = "Arial", gravity = "center")

text2 <- image_blank(width = 500, height = 150, color = "#ead61c") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "in time", color = "#000000", size = 60, font = "Arial", gravity = "west")

# generating left and right columns
left <- c(cry, text1) %>%
  image_append(stack = TRUE)

right <- c(cry, text2) %>%
  image_append(stack = TRUE)

# generating the final frame for the animation
frame5 <- c(left, right) %>%
  image_append()


# putting the frames in order using a vector
frames <- c(frame1, frame2, frame3, frame4, frame5)

# creating the animation
animated_meme <- image_animate(frames, fps = 0.5)

image_write(animated_meme, "my_animated_gif.gif")
